1
00:00:05,771 --> 00:00:07,401
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:07,471 --> 00:00:09,141
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:10,071 --> 00:00:12,111
You want to save
Taehan's Fashion Division, right?

4
00:00:12,911 --> 00:00:13,941
I need your help.

5
00:00:14,941 --> 00:00:16,241
But with Jun Hyeok,

6
00:00:16,941 --> 00:00:19,511
won't Director Baek be unable
to touch the Fashion Division now?

7
00:00:19,781 --> 00:00:21,411
This isn't about personal feelings.

8
00:00:22,121 --> 00:00:23,621
This is purely
for the good of the company.

9
00:00:23,981 --> 00:00:25,851
I'm proposing
a business partnership.

10
00:00:28,251 --> 00:00:29,661
What do you mean by that?

11
00:00:30,361 --> 00:00:32,061
Are you asking me
to come back to Taehan?

12
00:00:32,291 --> 00:00:36,001
No. I want you to launch
your own designer brand.

13
00:00:37,261 --> 00:00:38,261
What?

14
00:00:38,331 --> 00:00:42,201
I'll fund everything from operations
to production and manufacturing.

15
00:00:42,471 --> 00:00:43,801
All you have to do is design.

16
00:00:45,271 --> 00:00:47,241
What does launching a brand...

17
00:00:47,241 --> 00:00:49,311
have to do with
the Taehan Fashion Division?

18
00:00:49,781 --> 00:00:52,311
If this is just an excuse
to start something with me...

19
00:00:52,551 --> 00:00:55,581
I said this isn't personal.
It's a professional project.

20
00:00:56,151 --> 00:00:57,951
Then why in the world...

21
00:00:58,751 --> 00:01:00,621
are you making this offer to me?

22
00:01:00,921 --> 00:01:02,291
Because a Gong Ju Ah brand...

23
00:01:03,161 --> 00:01:05,421
will be the spark that revives
the Fashion Division.

24
00:01:06,161 --> 00:01:09,501
What are you talking about?
The Fashion Division is doing fine.

25
00:01:09,731 --> 00:01:11,361
What's there to revive?

26
00:01:11,661 --> 00:01:12,831
You'll find out soon enough.

27
00:01:14,771 --> 00:01:17,571
Review the proposal
and get back to me.

28
00:01:31,251 --> 00:01:32,551
- My goodness.
- Oh my.

29
00:01:35,051 --> 00:01:38,021
Ma'am, please look.
Do you recognize her?

30
00:01:47,731 --> 00:01:49,301
How could this be...

31
00:01:50,341 --> 00:01:52,671
Mom, do you know her?

32
00:01:53,011 --> 00:01:54,111
Wait, Jeong Han.

33
00:01:54,771 --> 00:01:56,541
I think I've seen that woman
somewhere before too.

34
00:01:57,441 --> 00:01:58,511
What?

35
00:01:59,651 --> 00:02:00,851
Yes, Detective Jang.

36
00:02:01,911 --> 00:02:05,591
Yes. All right,
I understand. Thank you. Yes.

37
00:02:06,891 --> 00:02:09,791
- The number is registered to...
- Jo Mi Hyang.

38
00:02:11,421 --> 00:02:12,891
That woman is Jo Mi Hyang.

39
00:02:14,091 --> 00:02:16,101
- What? Mom!
- Mom!

40
00:02:16,361 --> 00:02:17,501
- Mom!
- Mom!

41
00:02:18,261 --> 00:02:19,271
- Mom!
- Mom!

42
00:02:19,331 --> 00:02:20,331
- Stay with me, Mom!
- Mom!

43
00:02:20,401 --> 00:02:22,241
Who on earth is that woman, Mom?

44
00:02:22,301 --> 00:02:24,971
Mom, she's the one I saw, right?

45
00:02:25,871 --> 00:02:28,941
Jo Mi Hyang frequented the pharmacy,
pretending to be a regular.

46
00:02:29,541 --> 00:02:33,981
She kept tabs not just on family,
but on the search's progress.

47
00:02:34,481 --> 00:02:37,151
That's why she damaged the flyers,

48
00:02:37,221 --> 00:02:40,491
- and texted you to stop searching.
- No...

49
00:02:41,291 --> 00:02:44,361
How could she?
How could she do such a thing?

50
00:02:44,421 --> 00:02:47,961
But why? Why our father?

51
00:02:48,491 --> 00:02:50,301
- We're not sure either...
- First, we'll confirm...

52
00:02:50,301 --> 00:02:54,101
her address and start canvassing
the area around the pay phone.

53
00:02:55,031 --> 00:02:56,041
And one more thing.

54
00:02:56,441 --> 00:03:00,711
Please keep what you just found out
strictly within the family.

55
00:03:01,171 --> 00:03:02,611
If Jo Mi Hyang catches on,

56
00:03:02,911 --> 00:03:04,641
it could make tracking her
even more difficult.

57
00:03:05,041 --> 00:03:07,111
- Understood?
- Yes.

58
00:03:12,151 --> 00:03:13,151
- Slowly.
- Careful.

59
00:03:13,221 --> 00:03:14,721
Mother, are you okay?

60
00:03:17,361 --> 00:03:20,091
Honey, is it about Father?

61
00:03:20,991 --> 00:03:22,401
Yes, it is.

62
00:03:23,531 --> 00:03:25,801
It is? So you've found him?

63
00:03:26,331 --> 00:03:28,101
Honey, Mom isn't feeling well.

64
00:03:28,401 --> 00:03:30,641
- Let's get her inside to lie down.
- Right, okay.

65
00:03:31,101 --> 00:03:32,411
- Go on inside.
- Mother.

66
00:03:33,411 --> 00:03:34,411
Mom.

67
00:03:34,941 --> 00:03:36,011
Okay, this way.

68
00:03:39,011 --> 00:03:40,611
Honey, come. I need to talk to you.

69
00:03:49,321 --> 00:03:50,621
She's someone Mother knows?

70
00:03:51,561 --> 00:03:52,561
Yes.

71
00:03:53,091 --> 00:03:54,931
She's a regular at the pharmacy,
apparently.

72
00:03:55,491 --> 00:03:57,061
What is that supposed to mean?

73
00:03:57,501 --> 00:04:00,401
You mean she was hiding Father
and still coming to the pharmacy?

74
00:04:01,201 --> 00:04:03,001
It was more than just
coming and going.

75
00:04:03,571 --> 00:04:05,941
I found out she was interfering
with our search the whole time.

76
00:04:06,441 --> 00:04:09,611
Then what's their relationship?
Was your father having an affair?

77
00:04:09,941 --> 00:04:11,081
I don't think so.

78
00:04:11,881 --> 00:04:13,581
She's listed as his younger sister.

79
00:04:14,411 --> 00:04:16,581
And...

80
00:04:17,721 --> 00:04:19,351
And what? What is it?

81
00:04:21,091 --> 00:04:22,151
That woman...

82
00:04:23,921 --> 00:04:25,661
was beating Father.

83
00:04:28,531 --> 00:04:30,061
I should've kept looking for him.

84
00:04:32,231 --> 00:04:33,601
We'll find him, honey.

85
00:04:34,131 --> 00:04:35,701
We're so close now, okay?

86
00:04:40,871 --> 00:04:41,871
Honey.

87
00:04:42,811 --> 00:04:43,981
We're going to find him.

88
00:04:45,911 --> 00:04:48,151
Don't blame yourself, okay?

89
00:04:56,561 --> 00:04:58,491
He's not in Seongdam, though.

90
00:04:59,061 --> 00:05:02,701
I'm telling you,
I searched high and low.

91
00:05:03,531 --> 00:05:04,601
I know.

92
00:05:05,061 --> 00:05:07,801
I am sorry to have troubled you
for nothing, Mi Hyang.

93
00:05:12,711 --> 00:05:14,911
I'll be praying
you find him, Ms. Na.

94
00:05:29,061 --> 00:05:32,631
I made this for you.
I thought it'd suit you.

95
00:05:32,731 --> 00:05:36,961
Oh, it wasn't me.
My brother does most of the work.

96
00:05:45,201 --> 00:05:46,641
No, it can't be!

97
00:05:48,811 --> 00:05:50,181
My gosh, Mother!

98
00:05:51,041 --> 00:05:52,281
Mother, are you all right?

99
00:05:52,851 --> 00:05:54,381
Mother.

100
00:05:56,821 --> 00:05:57,851
Mother.

101
00:05:58,821 --> 00:05:59,891
This...

102
00:06:00,521 --> 00:06:02,091
Jeong Han's father made this.

103
00:06:02,721 --> 00:06:04,661
That woman gave this to me.

104
00:06:05,121 --> 00:06:06,431
My goodness!

105
00:06:07,361 --> 00:06:09,461
How did I not know, Seong Mi?

106
00:06:10,461 --> 00:06:13,971
I had no idea.
I was nothing but kind to her.

107
00:06:15,171 --> 00:06:16,371
To that woman...

108
00:06:18,071 --> 00:06:19,511
I told her we were searching,

109
00:06:20,111 --> 00:06:21,541
and I even asked her
to help us find him.

110
00:06:23,781 --> 00:06:26,751
She was always telling me
stories about her brother,

111
00:06:27,781 --> 00:06:31,051
but I never dreamed
he was Jeong Han's father.

112
00:06:31,721 --> 00:06:34,721
- Unbelievable.
- But why on earth would she?

113
00:06:36,561 --> 00:06:38,861
What did we do to deserve this?

114
00:06:39,291 --> 00:06:41,831
I just can't think
of any reason why.

115
00:06:42,731 --> 00:06:44,601
How could she?

116
00:06:45,361 --> 00:06:47,001
To just ruin someone's life...

117
00:06:48,231 --> 00:06:51,441
She saw our whole family
lose a father,

118
00:06:51,501 --> 00:06:54,271
and watched me live on
after losing my husband.

119
00:06:54,911 --> 00:06:56,941
How could she do such a thing
after seeing all that?

120
00:06:58,241 --> 00:07:00,911
- Mother.
- I just can't!

121
00:07:03,221 --> 00:07:05,721
Mother.

122
00:07:06,551 --> 00:07:07,991
- Mother.
- This is killing me.

123
00:07:08,051 --> 00:07:09,991
- Mother.
- I can't take this anymore!

124
00:07:12,391 --> 00:07:15,091
We only have a few more days
of you walking me home like this.

125
00:07:16,461 --> 00:07:19,601
It still doesn't feel real
that we'll be living together.

126
00:07:20,931 --> 00:07:22,301
Are you sure you're okay...

127
00:07:23,101 --> 00:07:24,101
with not having a ceremony?

128
00:07:24,171 --> 00:07:28,971
Yes. A family photo with Ji Hu
is all I need.

129
00:07:29,841 --> 00:07:30,941
The day after tomorrow, right?

130
00:07:31,241 --> 00:07:35,081
Yes. Hyun Bin wants to meet me
about a gift tomorrow.

131
00:07:35,151 --> 00:07:37,151
- Are you free then?
- What?

132
00:07:37,421 --> 00:07:38,421
Yes.

133
00:07:39,691 --> 00:07:40,691
Honey.

134
00:07:43,261 --> 00:07:44,391
Something's wrong.

135
00:07:45,091 --> 00:07:46,091
Isn't there?

136
00:07:46,861 --> 00:07:47,861
It's just...

137
00:07:50,801 --> 00:07:52,631
Gi Cheol lost his memory?

138
00:07:53,431 --> 00:07:56,071
Yes. Apparently,
some woman took him in,

139
00:07:56,141 --> 00:08:00,271
and for 30 years, he was her brother
and she made him work.

140
00:08:00,411 --> 00:08:01,971
That wretched woman...

141
00:08:02,681 --> 00:08:06,811
I know. I thought
that only happened on TV.

142
00:08:07,111 --> 00:08:09,321
We could've found him
so much sooner.

143
00:08:10,221 --> 00:08:13,391
If only he hadn't disappeared
on the very same day as your mother.

144
00:08:14,391 --> 00:08:15,621
Father, please.

145
00:08:15,991 --> 00:08:18,321
What have I done to both of them?

146
00:08:21,791 --> 00:08:23,761
How could anyone
do something like that?

147
00:08:24,161 --> 00:08:25,531
The nerve of her.

148
00:08:25,861 --> 00:08:28,501
I can't stop picturing her face,
and it's driving me crazy.

149
00:08:29,171 --> 00:08:31,541
Is Grandfather safe?
Does he look healthy?

150
00:08:31,901 --> 00:08:35,071
I don't know.
Just from the CCTV footage,

151
00:08:35,711 --> 00:08:37,611
I can't get a sense of
what his life is like.

152
00:08:38,711 --> 00:08:39,851
Since he lost his memory,

153
00:08:39,851 --> 00:08:42,081
she must have manipulated him
into depending on her.

154
00:08:42,551 --> 00:08:45,321
He was always so high-spirited
and larger than life.

155
00:08:46,851 --> 00:08:48,391
Seeing him like that just...

156
00:08:50,191 --> 00:08:51,221
Uncle.

157
00:08:51,291 --> 00:08:54,731
My father was
such a brilliant doctor, you know.

158
00:08:55,291 --> 00:08:58,131
How could anyone take a man
like that and do this to him?

159
00:09:27,761 --> 00:09:29,401
I told you never to go outside!

160
00:09:29,861 --> 00:09:32,261
What were you thinking?
What if the police caught you?

161
00:09:36,001 --> 00:09:38,001
We're actually looking for
our father right now.

162
00:10:19,611 --> 00:10:22,011
(Gong Gi Cheol)

163
00:10:54,951 --> 00:10:58,881
Mom, with psychological tests,
you're not meant to overthink them.

164
00:10:59,021 --> 00:11:02,321
The results are most accurate
if you go with your first instinct.

165
00:11:02,421 --> 00:11:05,991
Really? Okay.
I should listen to the med student.

166
00:11:06,861 --> 00:11:10,501
I'm already getting nervous
about my session tomorrow.

167
00:11:12,461 --> 00:11:16,971
- Are you sleeping here tonight?
- I am. Why?

168
00:11:17,271 --> 00:11:18,701
Honestly.

169
00:11:19,201 --> 00:11:23,281
I thought couples sleep in one bed
even when they're mad at each other.

170
00:11:23,411 --> 00:11:26,511
My goodness. Listen to you.
What do you know about it?

171
00:11:28,251 --> 00:11:32,721
I need you two to make up
so I can leave for the US in peace.

172
00:11:32,791 --> 00:11:34,291
I'm leaving in just a few days.

173
00:11:34,491 --> 00:11:38,861
Fine, I get it. I'll try.
No, I am trying, okay?

174
00:11:38,991 --> 00:11:39,991
Okay.

175
00:11:41,961 --> 00:11:43,401
Dr. Yang.

176
00:11:46,371 --> 00:11:48,001
Hey, Min Seo.

177
00:11:48,631 --> 00:11:50,271
Share this with your mom.

178
00:11:50,671 --> 00:11:52,271
Thank you, Dr. Yang.

179
00:11:53,341 --> 00:11:55,611
Enjoy. Honey.

180
00:11:59,711 --> 00:12:01,011
Se Ri...

181
00:12:08,421 --> 00:12:09,421
See?

182
00:12:10,561 --> 00:12:12,021
She won't even look at me.

183
00:12:12,291 --> 00:12:16,831
You should've said you waited
an hour to get those cookies.

184
00:12:17,001 --> 00:12:18,031
Forget it.

185
00:12:18,031 --> 00:12:20,471
Gosh, don't give up
because she's ignoring you.

186
00:12:20,471 --> 00:12:23,041
Be persistent
and try every day. Got it?

187
00:12:23,641 --> 00:12:27,171
- Okay.
- Let's visit Auntie as we're here.

188
00:12:27,841 --> 00:12:29,371
Your aunt? Why?

189
00:12:31,081 --> 00:12:34,151
- What? You're still sleeping apart?
- Auntie...

190
00:12:34,211 --> 00:12:35,381
Okay, I get it.

191
00:12:35,681 --> 00:12:37,881
I thought things had gotten better
after that big talk.

192
00:12:38,251 --> 00:12:40,691
She just can't seem to let go
of her resentment toward me.

193
00:12:41,621 --> 00:12:43,561
She can't even stand
to lie down next to me.

194
00:12:44,161 --> 00:12:46,331
Gosh, what are we going to do?

195
00:12:47,131 --> 00:12:48,861
So, what was it
you wanted to tell me?

196
00:12:49,061 --> 00:12:51,961
Min Seo gave me a great idea
to help her mom and dad make up.

197
00:12:52,031 --> 00:12:55,071
- A brilliant idea, in fact.
- Really?

198
00:12:55,071 --> 00:12:56,071
Yes.

199
00:12:56,131 --> 00:13:00,171
- But we need your help, Auntie.
- Me? What do you need me to do?

200
00:13:10,421 --> 00:13:13,291
Why the long faces, everyone?
Let's eat.

201
00:13:16,691 --> 00:13:21,091
Let's get through our days
with a prayerful heart.

202
00:13:21,791 --> 00:13:23,561
That's what we need to do.
All right?

203
00:13:24,131 --> 00:13:26,331
Dae Han, you focus
on preparing to move in.

204
00:13:26,771 --> 00:13:29,071
Seong Mi, you take good care
of your health.

205
00:13:29,801 --> 00:13:34,011
Everyone, just keep doing your part
and carry on.

206
00:13:34,941 --> 00:13:36,781
That's what Father would want.

207
00:13:37,681 --> 00:13:38,941
- Yes, Mother.
- Yes.

208
00:13:40,211 --> 00:13:41,381
I didn't endure...

209
00:13:42,081 --> 00:13:44,581
the last 30 years for nothing.

210
00:13:45,181 --> 00:13:49,391
I'm not going to break down now.
Not ever.

211
00:13:50,621 --> 00:13:51,661
Okay?

212
00:13:52,421 --> 00:13:56,061
We're so close.
We'll find him soon, I promise.

213
00:13:56,401 --> 00:13:58,401
Yes, let's hold on to that.

214
00:14:00,171 --> 00:14:02,231
I'm all right,
so I need you all to be strong.

215
00:14:02,501 --> 00:14:03,501
Okay?

216
00:14:04,471 --> 00:14:05,471
Yes, Mother.

217
00:14:06,171 --> 00:14:07,171
Woo Jae.

218
00:14:09,471 --> 00:14:10,481
Okay.

219
00:14:19,821 --> 00:14:20,821
Well...

220
00:14:20,821 --> 00:14:23,621
I heard you're starting counseling
for the "Bucket" couple today.

221
00:14:24,061 --> 00:14:25,061
Yes.

222
00:14:25,961 --> 00:14:30,801
- Be strong. Mom is trying her best.
- Yes, I have to.

223
00:14:31,161 --> 00:14:34,231
Woo Jae said he's taking Mom out
for some fresh air.

224
00:14:34,571 --> 00:14:36,031
Are you heading out?

225
00:14:36,341 --> 00:14:38,441
I'm going to head over
to the police substation.

226
00:14:39,001 --> 00:14:43,511
I have no appointments this weekend,
and I'd just get anxious at home.

227
00:14:44,111 --> 00:14:47,651
Your father didn't have
his memories for a long time,

228
00:14:47,911 --> 00:14:50,751
and it seems he was being
gaslighted the whole time.

229
00:14:51,221 --> 00:14:55,351
When he's back, I'll do everything
I can to focus on his treatment.

230
00:14:55,851 --> 00:14:56,861
Okay.

231
00:14:57,421 --> 00:14:58,561
Thank you.

232
00:14:59,191 --> 00:15:01,861
- Hang in there, honey. Okay?
- Yes.

233
00:15:08,801 --> 00:15:12,341
Oh, what's this?
You're almost done already?

234
00:15:13,311 --> 00:15:15,211
You're the head designer
for a reason, aren't you?

235
00:15:15,841 --> 00:15:19,951
- Here.
- What's this? I have my own card.

236
00:15:20,051 --> 00:15:23,381
You're taking Grandma out, right?
Treat her to something nice...

237
00:15:23,421 --> 00:15:25,381
and try to cheer her up. Okay?

238
00:15:25,781 --> 00:15:29,051
I have to finish this up
and get ready for my interview.

239
00:15:29,821 --> 00:15:33,191
Okay, got it. You focus on work.
Thanks for the card. See you later.

240
00:15:33,261 --> 00:15:34,261
Okay.

241
00:15:39,431 --> 00:15:40,431
Hello?

242
00:15:40,831 --> 00:15:42,001
Hello.

243
00:15:42,371 --> 00:15:44,671
This is Choi Ha Jin,
the managing director at Harben.

244
00:15:45,541 --> 00:15:47,741
Yes. Hello.

245
00:15:48,141 --> 00:15:51,711
Would you be available
to meet for coffee today?

246
00:15:57,921 --> 00:16:00,751
I want you to launch
your own designer brand.

247
00:16:01,951 --> 00:16:04,121
Why is he being like this?

248
00:16:05,661 --> 00:16:07,191
Because a Gong Ju Ah brand...

249
00:16:07,191 --> 00:16:09,661
will be the spark that revives
the Fashion Division.

250
00:16:10,201 --> 00:16:13,671
What are you talking about?
The Fashion Division is doing fine.

251
00:16:13,831 --> 00:16:15,701
What's there to revive?

252
00:16:15,701 --> 00:16:17,201
You'll find out soon enough.

253
00:16:17,701 --> 00:16:20,571
Gosh, what is he even talking about?

254
00:16:21,141 --> 00:16:22,411
Unbelievable.

255
00:16:35,521 --> 00:16:38,161
Ms. Gong!
I'm at the office right now.

256
00:16:38,291 --> 00:16:41,531
Right. Since the new product launch
is coming up,

257
00:16:41,661 --> 00:16:43,401
you had to come in on a weekend?

258
00:16:43,661 --> 00:16:46,261
Yes, the rest of the team
will be here soon.

259
00:16:46,571 --> 00:16:51,471
So Hye, is something going on
at the company?

260
00:16:52,041 --> 00:16:53,041
Not really.

261
00:16:53,441 --> 00:16:55,911
Other than Mr. Park turning out
to be the Chairman's son,

262
00:16:55,971 --> 00:16:58,541
and the Chairman passing away,
what else could there be?

263
00:16:58,711 --> 00:17:01,251
Never mind. I was just curious.

264
00:17:03,221 --> 00:17:04,821
But hey, Ms. Gong,

265
00:17:05,121 --> 00:17:08,591
- are you really going to Harben?
- I don't know yet.

266
00:17:08,721 --> 00:17:12,991
I might just launch
my own brand, or something.

267
00:17:13,531 --> 00:17:15,961
That's amazing! For real?

268
00:17:16,291 --> 00:17:19,771
I told you nothing's certain yet.
I'll let you know when it is.

269
00:17:20,001 --> 00:17:21,971
Okay, I'll let you get back to it.
Bye.

270
00:17:32,081 --> 00:17:34,711
- Hello?
- Have you reviewed the proposal?

271
00:17:35,351 --> 00:17:38,681
No. You just gave it to me yesterday
and you're already asking?

272
00:17:38,921 --> 00:17:40,191
Because I'm in a rush.

273
00:17:40,991 --> 00:17:45,161
Even so, how can I make
such a huge decision overnight?

274
00:17:45,261 --> 00:17:47,491
What's the hesitation?
What's the problem?

275
00:17:48,131 --> 00:17:51,431
Just wait. I have a meeting
with Harben today, too.

276
00:17:51,501 --> 00:17:53,331
Then meet with me after you're done.

277
00:17:53,931 --> 00:17:56,941
- What?
- Text me a time and place.

278
00:17:59,041 --> 00:18:00,611
Hello?

279
00:18:01,171 --> 00:18:03,341
Gosh, what is with him?

280
00:18:04,511 --> 00:18:07,181
Anyway, talk about a cold shoulder.

281
00:18:07,511 --> 00:18:10,651
Is he really this different
from when we were dating? Gosh.

282
00:18:11,421 --> 00:18:13,321
What's this? Wow.

283
00:18:14,321 --> 00:18:16,121
Our nephew has good taste,
doesn't he?

284
00:18:16,121 --> 00:18:17,191
He sure does.

285
00:18:19,091 --> 00:18:21,061
- Oh, Hyun Bin!
- Hey.

286
00:18:22,631 --> 00:18:25,401
Seriously, what gift requires us
to come all this way?

287
00:18:25,461 --> 00:18:27,501
I know, right?
A busy guy like you...

288
00:18:27,571 --> 00:18:30,471
As a wedding gift, I wanted to redo
your room for you.

289
00:18:30,871 --> 00:18:34,411
- You shouldn't have. It's too much.
- Let's go.

290
00:18:37,881 --> 00:18:38,881
What's up with him?

291
00:18:39,741 --> 00:18:41,081
Is something wrong?

292
00:18:41,711 --> 00:18:43,981
He's been like that ever since
he and Ju Ah broke up.

293
00:18:48,521 --> 00:18:50,361
Oh my gosh!

294
00:18:51,691 --> 00:18:54,561
You really didn't have to go
to all this trouble.

295
00:18:54,731 --> 00:18:57,131
I thought a lot about this gift,
so please, accept it.

296
00:18:57,701 --> 00:19:00,331
We'll at least take a look
around then.

297
00:19:00,401 --> 00:19:05,201
This place is so chic.
This style must be in right now.

298
00:19:05,301 --> 00:19:09,411
Yes. They have a variety of designs,
so please, take your time.

299
00:19:09,941 --> 00:19:13,311
This is amazing.
The frames are so thin.

300
00:19:13,651 --> 00:19:16,651
The slim frame design
maximizes the viewing area,

301
00:19:16,751 --> 00:19:20,191
so you can enjoy a wide panorama.
The insulation is great too.

302
00:19:20,351 --> 00:19:23,221
I see. The design is so elegant,

303
00:19:23,391 --> 00:19:25,161
and it would make the whole house
feel so open.

304
00:19:25,421 --> 00:19:26,761
I'd like to look around
a little more.

305
00:19:26,831 --> 00:19:30,501
- Take your time. I'm here to help.
- Okay.

306
00:19:32,401 --> 00:19:33,931
Oh my.

307
00:19:35,501 --> 00:19:37,241
This is incredible.

308
00:19:39,341 --> 00:19:40,371
Hyun Bin.

309
00:19:40,811 --> 00:19:42,341
Are you upset with me
about something?

310
00:19:42,741 --> 00:19:46,141
- Excuse me?
- I had no idea you two were dating.

311
00:19:47,981 --> 00:19:50,021
I feel bad about
going to her family...

312
00:19:51,081 --> 00:19:52,681
and asking for their blessing.
I feel I stepped out of line.

313
00:19:54,121 --> 00:19:55,721
Don't worry about it.

314
00:19:55,721 --> 00:19:58,861
We've already broken up,
and I'm over Gong Ju Ah.

315
00:19:59,491 --> 00:20:01,061
- But...
- Excuse me.

316
00:20:04,031 --> 00:20:05,331
Yes, this is Yang Hyun Bin speaking.

317
00:20:05,961 --> 00:20:07,201
Yes.

318
00:20:12,541 --> 00:20:14,211
He sure looks like
he's not over her.

319
00:20:14,911 --> 00:20:16,311
He is so not over her.

320
00:20:17,011 --> 00:20:18,241
That's what I was thinking.

321
00:20:20,111 --> 00:20:23,151
Mom, I'm heading out. Oh my.

322
00:20:24,551 --> 00:20:26,521
What's with the big reaction?

323
00:20:26,691 --> 00:20:29,251
Seriously.
One would think you saw a ghost.

324
00:20:29,921 --> 00:20:31,121
Hello.

325
00:20:32,021 --> 00:20:35,831
Well, well. To what do we owe
this greeting from a classless brat?

326
00:20:36,031 --> 00:20:38,961
Wow, Dr. Han.
You sure know how to hold a grudge.

327
00:20:40,071 --> 00:20:42,771
I have somewhere to be,
so I'm going to head out.

328
00:20:46,001 --> 00:20:47,641
- Sit down.
- Okay.

329
00:20:48,341 --> 00:20:52,281
Dr. Han, is it normal for couples
to have separate sessions?

330
00:20:52,611 --> 00:20:57,151
There are many approaches,
but I felt you needed separate ones.

331
00:20:58,221 --> 00:21:02,521
First, what's your ultimate goal
for this counseling?

332
00:21:03,421 --> 00:21:07,731
I don't know.
I'm just here because I was told to.

333
00:21:08,731 --> 00:21:11,831
Your husband said he wants
to resolve your conflicts...

334
00:21:11,931 --> 00:21:14,101
and repair your relationship.

335
00:21:15,501 --> 00:21:18,101
You want that as well, don't you?

336
00:21:19,901 --> 00:21:20,911
Yes.

337
00:21:24,641 --> 00:21:25,741
That's a relief.

338
00:21:26,781 --> 00:21:29,281
She's been
cold-shouldering me lately,

339
00:21:29,981 --> 00:21:32,981
I was worried she might
actually want a divorce.

340
00:21:34,721 --> 00:21:37,821
Actually, you two have
something in common.

341
00:21:38,821 --> 00:21:43,701
You both share a deep-seated fear
of losing each other.

342
00:21:44,301 --> 00:21:47,531
And you've both managed that anxiety
through intense affection.

343
00:21:48,571 --> 00:21:49,571
That's right.

344
00:21:50,101 --> 00:21:54,741
At first, that common ground
probably made you both feel secure.

345
00:21:57,311 --> 00:21:59,481
The problem is when that anxiety
flares up,

346
00:21:59,541 --> 00:22:03,211
your ways of coping are
polar opposites.

347
00:22:03,821 --> 00:22:05,781
Really?

348
00:22:06,081 --> 00:22:10,491
When anxious, your instinct is
to try and control the situation.

349
00:22:10,961 --> 00:22:12,461
Hiring the private detective,
for example,

350
00:22:12,721 --> 00:22:15,361
was a way to ease your anxiety
through control.

351
00:22:17,501 --> 00:22:18,861
I see.

352
00:22:19,431 --> 00:22:22,101
You, on the other hand,
when you feel anxious,

353
00:22:22,171 --> 00:22:25,771
tend to become more devoted
to your husband and family.

354
00:22:26,001 --> 00:22:28,671
That's how you regain
your sense of security.

355
00:22:29,941 --> 00:22:33,381
The reason you were so furious
about the private detective...

356
00:22:33,751 --> 00:22:38,681
is that it felt like a rejection
of all that devotion.

357
00:22:39,981 --> 00:22:42,451
That wasn't my intention.

358
00:22:43,251 --> 00:22:47,991
Also, your evaluation showed
a tendency toward self-effacement.

359
00:22:49,391 --> 00:22:51,001
What does that mean?

360
00:22:51,331 --> 00:22:56,371
You put your family's wishes first,
rather than your own feelings.

361
00:22:56,871 --> 00:22:59,871
Because you feel you must be needed
in order to be loved,

362
00:23:00,271 --> 00:23:04,541
so you'll go to any lengths
when it comes to your family.

363
00:23:04,911 --> 00:23:09,251
Even if it means sacrificing
or harming yourself.

364
00:23:13,051 --> 00:23:16,191
Think back to the past incidents
involving my family.

365
00:23:17,791 --> 00:23:18,791
Right.

366
00:23:19,221 --> 00:23:23,391
What can I do
to make things right with my wife?

367
00:23:24,201 --> 00:23:26,531
I really am trying my best.

368
00:23:27,131 --> 00:23:28,931
I try to make her happy every day,

369
00:23:29,471 --> 00:23:30,841
I tell her how I feel,

370
00:23:31,341 --> 00:23:34,041
- and I plan special events for her.
- What's important...

371
00:23:34,371 --> 00:23:38,181
is that you recognize and respond
to your wife's emotions.

372
00:23:40,581 --> 00:23:42,611
How am I supposed
to know what she's feeling...

373
00:23:43,921 --> 00:23:44,951
Right.

374
00:23:45,651 --> 00:23:48,651
Recognize and respond
to her emotions.

375
00:23:49,651 --> 00:23:53,091
All this time, you've been
trying to please your family,

376
00:23:53,561 --> 00:23:55,961
but you ended up feeling all alone.

377
00:23:56,901 --> 00:24:01,231
You probably couldn't even show
the pain or hurt you felt inside.

378
00:24:04,641 --> 00:24:06,241
From now on,

379
00:24:06,671 --> 00:24:10,341
practice speaking up
about what you truly want.

380
00:24:10,811 --> 00:24:14,511
Then your relationship will
naturally start to heal.

381
00:24:16,811 --> 00:24:19,251
Speak up about what I truly want.

382
00:24:21,551 --> 00:24:23,121
I understand, Dr. Han.

383
00:24:29,461 --> 00:24:31,831
I wonder if their counseling session
is going well.

384
00:24:32,661 --> 00:24:34,171
I'm sure they're doing fine.

385
00:24:34,971 --> 00:24:37,571
When I saw Mom yesterday,
she seemed really serious about it.

386
00:24:38,571 --> 00:24:43,781
Wouldn't it be great to live
together as sisters, chatting?

387
00:24:45,341 --> 00:24:49,811
When you go to the US, promise to
video call me twice a day.

388
00:24:50,521 --> 00:24:51,651
Okay.

389
00:24:52,421 --> 00:24:55,421
You should also get
that consulting from Jason...

390
00:24:55,521 --> 00:24:57,691
and make sure you achieve
your dream, okay?

391
00:24:58,161 --> 00:25:01,091
I promise I'll succeed
and be a sister you can be proud of.

392
00:25:01,831 --> 00:25:03,461
You're already more than enough.

393
00:25:04,231 --> 00:25:08,431
Right. About Ji Hu's tutoring.
Woo Jae will do it here.

394
00:25:09,401 --> 00:25:13,241
What? I said I didn't want him here.
Didn't you tell Woo Jae?

395
00:25:13,711 --> 00:25:17,811
- I told him you were uncomfortable.
- And?

396
00:25:17,881 --> 00:25:19,711
I don't know. That's just what
Woo Jae said he was going to do.

397
00:25:19,741 --> 00:25:21,581
Seriously, why?

398
00:25:22,581 --> 00:25:23,581
I don't know.

399
00:25:23,821 --> 00:25:27,621
Seriously, if Woo Jae keeps coming,
I'll keep running into him.

400
00:25:27,991 --> 00:25:30,791
I was clear I don't want to see him.
I thought he'd get the message.

401
00:25:32,121 --> 00:25:36,261
Is this his way of getting revenge
for me annoying him all this time?

402
00:25:47,871 --> 00:25:48,871
Grandma.

403
00:25:53,751 --> 00:25:54,811
Have some of this.

404
00:26:00,721 --> 00:26:03,251
You're going to so much trouble,
worrying about me.

405
00:26:03,691 --> 00:26:05,391
Don't say that.

406
00:26:05,761 --> 00:26:07,661
Besides, I'm happy to be on a date
with my grandma.

407
00:26:12,861 --> 00:26:14,901
I wonder if his memories
will ever come back.

408
00:26:16,301 --> 00:26:18,101
Even if he comes back home,

409
00:26:19,201 --> 00:26:21,841
what if he still doesn't
remember anything?

410
00:26:28,451 --> 00:26:29,451
Grandma.

411
00:26:30,921 --> 00:26:32,751
My professor once said...

412
00:26:33,221 --> 00:26:37,521
that since memory's tied to emotion,
family faces are the last to fade.

413
00:26:38,561 --> 00:26:40,691
When he sees you,
I'm sure he'll remember something.

414
00:26:41,131 --> 00:26:43,901
Just like he recalled the hospital
after seeing the broadcast.

415
00:26:47,431 --> 00:26:48,431
You think so?

416
00:26:48,801 --> 00:26:49,801
Yes.

417
00:26:50,671 --> 00:26:51,871
Try some of this.

418
00:27:05,981 --> 00:27:08,221
I know you must be anxious.

419
00:27:08,991 --> 00:27:09,991
No, I'm all right.

420
00:27:10,961 --> 00:27:11,961
Gosh.

421
00:27:12,561 --> 00:27:15,091
I feel like I'm just getting
in the way.

422
00:27:15,391 --> 00:27:19,761
- I'm getting in the way, aren't I?
- No, not at all. I understand.

423
00:27:20,301 --> 00:27:22,531
We're running a background check
on Jo Mi Hyang now,

424
00:27:22,601 --> 00:27:26,001
and we're digging into everything
her address, associates, all of it.

425
00:27:26,301 --> 00:27:27,571
Okay. Good.

426
00:27:27,841 --> 00:27:29,371
Yes, got it. Okay.

427
00:27:32,911 --> 00:27:35,251
We've started a joint operation
with the Seongdam Police detectives.

428
00:27:35,611 --> 00:27:38,881
Plainclothes officers are canvassing
the area, starting at the payphone.

429
00:27:39,221 --> 00:27:42,991
Once we can track her movements,
we'll find her in no time.

430
00:27:43,151 --> 00:27:46,461
Really? Thank you.
Thank you so much.

431
00:27:51,161 --> 00:27:55,201
I thought the interview was Monday.
Was it rescheduled?

432
00:27:55,701 --> 00:27:58,901
No. The interview is
just a formality, anyway.

433
00:27:59,301 --> 00:28:02,971
I wanted to talk with you beforehand
about the direction of our brand.

434
00:28:03,341 --> 00:28:04,941
I see.

435
00:28:05,811 --> 00:28:10,351
You know FG's Hot Summer Collection
hurt our sales at Harben, right?

436
00:28:10,781 --> 00:28:13,321
I see.

437
00:28:13,821 --> 00:28:18,821
How you took the stagnant FG brand
and made it a market leader again...

438
00:28:19,091 --> 00:28:24,161
We're desperate for your know-how
and strategies for success.

439
00:28:27,031 --> 00:28:31,101
What new direction do you envision
for Harben, Director?

440
00:28:31,341 --> 00:28:33,241
My goal is clear.

441
00:28:33,741 --> 00:28:36,171
To break into the industry's
top three by next season.

442
00:28:37,641 --> 00:28:40,481
- I see...
- In the end, fashion is a business.

443
00:28:41,211 --> 00:28:44,451
A brand's value is based on
numbers and sales data.

444
00:28:44,581 --> 00:28:45,721
That's what proves it.

445
00:29:00,401 --> 00:29:01,831
So, how'd it go with Harben?

446
00:29:03,071 --> 00:29:04,801
Just tell me why you wanted me
to meet them.

447
00:29:05,241 --> 00:29:08,541
I made you an offer that's hard
for any designer to refuse,

448
00:29:08,611 --> 00:29:10,541
so I want to know
why you're hesitating.

449
00:29:12,611 --> 00:29:15,081
It's a tempting offer,

450
00:29:15,651 --> 00:29:18,281
but honestly,
I'm not sure I can do it.

451
00:29:18,751 --> 00:29:21,921
- I'm not prepared at all...
- Just focus on the design.

452
00:29:22,191 --> 00:29:24,061
I'll take care of everything else.

453
00:29:25,091 --> 00:29:27,121
That's why I'm even more hesitant.

454
00:29:27,391 --> 00:29:31,661
If this brand were my own,
only I'd be to blame if it failed.

455
00:29:31,901 --> 00:29:33,531
But this is different.

456
00:29:34,101 --> 00:29:37,301
I'm just not sure my abilities...

457
00:29:37,371 --> 00:29:39,241
have been proven enough
to handle a whole brand.

458
00:29:39,501 --> 00:29:41,811
Didn't you read what I wrote
in your recommendation to Harben?

459
00:29:42,371 --> 00:29:46,011
Unparalleled design sense,
excellent project leadership skills,

460
00:29:46,241 --> 00:29:50,821
and the drive to always get results,
even in a crisis. That's you.

461
00:29:51,721 --> 00:29:53,221
Why are you being like this?

462
00:29:53,481 --> 00:29:56,451
Is this because you feel guilty
that I quit because of you?

463
00:29:56,821 --> 00:29:58,091
You asked me to protect...

464
00:29:58,091 --> 00:30:00,631
the Taehan Fashion Division,
didn't you?

465
00:30:00,891 --> 00:30:03,631
That's what I'm doing right now
protecting the Fashion Division.

466
00:30:04,931 --> 00:30:07,061
No, I mean...

467
00:30:07,301 --> 00:30:10,031
What on earth does that have
to do with this?

468
00:30:10,101 --> 00:30:11,841
I can't explain everything
right now.

469
00:30:18,411 --> 00:30:20,951
Are you sure?
That you're really over me?

470
00:30:21,811 --> 00:30:24,021
I'm sure. I'm solely...

471
00:30:24,081 --> 00:30:26,181
making this offer based on
a business decision.

472
00:30:26,621 --> 00:30:30,591
So I need you to think about it
from a business perspective, too.

473
00:30:31,121 --> 00:30:34,261
- It won't be an easy road.
- I'm Pacu Nacho.

474
00:30:34,591 --> 00:30:38,861
Known for my trend-setting branding
and unique marketing.

475
00:30:38,931 --> 00:30:40,901
The brand director, Pacu Nacho Yang.

476
00:30:46,341 --> 00:30:49,411
I'd like your answer by tomorrow.
I'll be at my parents' house.

477
00:30:49,841 --> 00:30:50,941
Wait, but...

478
00:30:54,351 --> 00:30:55,351
Unbelievable...

479
00:30:57,881 --> 00:30:58,881
Hey, Ju Ah.

480
00:30:59,521 --> 00:31:00,521
Where've you been?

481
00:31:00,591 --> 00:31:04,591
- An interview. And you, Uncle?
- The police substation.

482
00:31:04,891 --> 00:31:07,361
Why? Did something happen?
Did they find Grandfather?

483
00:31:07,431 --> 00:31:10,191
No, I was just curious
if there's been any progress.

484
00:31:10,601 --> 00:31:12,161
Your dad has been
at the substation all day,

485
00:31:12,231 --> 00:31:14,871
so I'll stop by Dong Suk's shop,
then head over.

486
00:31:15,571 --> 00:31:18,401
- Uncle, hang on one second.
- Why?

487
00:31:18,471 --> 00:31:21,211
I finished the matching pajamas.
Let me go get them.

488
00:31:21,271 --> 00:31:23,341
Could you show them
to Dong Suk? Wait here.

489
00:31:27,351 --> 00:31:29,581
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

490
00:31:30,821 --> 00:31:34,991
If you dislike the size or design,
I might need to make adjustments,

491
00:31:35,051 --> 00:31:36,251
so I didn't wrap them.

492
00:31:40,791 --> 00:31:42,361
My goodness!

493
00:31:42,661 --> 00:31:43,891
Oh my.

494
00:31:44,501 --> 00:31:47,601
- Do you like them?
- Like them? I love them!

495
00:31:48,231 --> 00:31:49,871
They're so beautiful.

496
00:31:50,431 --> 00:31:54,141
- How did you make these so quickly?
- Our Ju Ah,

497
00:31:54,641 --> 00:31:58,781
- she's amazing, isn't she?
- Yes. They're too precious to wear.

498
00:31:58,911 --> 00:32:01,411
- Honey, how do these look on me?
- Let me see.

499
00:32:02,281 --> 00:32:04,781
They look amazing on you.
You're so beautiful.

500
00:32:06,221 --> 00:32:07,421
Thank you, niece.

501
00:32:08,351 --> 00:32:10,721
I'm just so, so happy.

502
00:32:11,691 --> 00:32:13,561
Dolphin, how do I look?
Come on, look. How do I look?

503
00:32:13,761 --> 00:32:15,091
Cute, cute. They look great on you.

504
00:32:15,491 --> 00:32:17,731
- They look great?
- They look great. Me too!

505
00:32:17,801 --> 00:32:19,901
- You try them on too, Dolphin.
- Should I?

506
00:32:21,801 --> 00:32:23,001
You know,

507
00:32:23,531 --> 00:32:25,641
I love seeing people happy
in the clothes I make.

508
00:32:25,771 --> 00:32:29,541
I love making people happy.

509
00:32:30,371 --> 00:32:31,741
That's admirable.

510
00:32:32,481 --> 00:32:35,351
Someone who creates happiness.

511
00:32:38,481 --> 00:32:39,481
Hey, Ju Ah.

512
00:32:40,651 --> 00:32:43,221
- Thanks, Ju Ah.
- Thank you, niece.

513
00:32:45,191 --> 00:32:46,191
You look beautiful.

514
00:32:49,131 --> 00:32:51,461
What's this? Isn't Min Seo's
farewell party tomorrow?

515
00:32:51,861 --> 00:32:54,971
That's why I'm here.
I can't make it to the party.

516
00:32:56,271 --> 00:32:59,101
Here, this is
a little something from me.

517
00:33:00,201 --> 00:33:03,471
I was going to get you a gift,
but at your age, cash is best.

518
00:33:04,381 --> 00:33:05,411
Money.

519
00:33:06,011 --> 00:33:08,151
- No, I couldn't...
- Just take it.

520
00:33:09,111 --> 00:33:10,381
Thank you.

521
00:33:11,821 --> 00:33:13,251
Make sure you call Mom often.

522
00:33:13,651 --> 00:33:14,651
I will.

523
00:33:15,051 --> 00:33:18,461
- Are you free tomorrow afternoon?
- No. It's the chairman's funeral.

524
00:33:18,821 --> 00:33:20,221
It's about Mom and Dad, though.

525
00:33:20,661 --> 00:33:21,691
I don't have time.

526
00:33:22,291 --> 00:33:26,231
Then why not just go to Argentina?
You don't do your duty here anyway.

527
00:33:26,531 --> 00:33:30,601
What are you talking about?
I play my part as a son, a grandson,

528
00:33:30,671 --> 00:33:33,341
a brother, and a nephew.
I do it all.

529
00:33:33,401 --> 00:33:34,671
Gosh, so hostile.

530
00:33:34,971 --> 00:33:38,641
- Something has gotten into you.
- Unbelievable.

531
00:33:39,381 --> 00:33:41,011
So what's the deal with Mom and Dad?

532
00:33:41,381 --> 00:33:44,681
Mom and Dr. Yang
still aren't getting along.

533
00:33:44,781 --> 00:33:48,951
They're not? Why not?
But Mom's back home, isn't she?

534
00:33:49,391 --> 00:33:52,361
What good is that?
They're sleeping in separate rooms.

535
00:33:52,661 --> 00:33:54,931
What? Separate rooms?

536
00:34:04,201 --> 00:34:05,201
Father!

537
00:34:07,171 --> 00:34:10,981
See, Grandfather? Look.
Mom is disobeying your orders.

538
00:34:11,041 --> 00:34:13,011
She's been sneaking upstairs
to sleep every night.

539
00:34:13,311 --> 00:34:14,751
How could you!

540
00:34:14,811 --> 00:34:17,651
I even saw her come out
with her pillow the other day.

541
00:34:18,981 --> 00:34:19,981
What did I tell you?

542
00:34:20,521 --> 00:34:22,621
If you're not getting a divorce,
then no matter how much you fight,

543
00:34:23,251 --> 00:34:24,391
I told you to share a bed.

544
00:34:25,621 --> 00:34:28,291
- Father...
- Go inside.

545
00:34:30,491 --> 00:34:32,661
And don't even think about
sneaking out again.

546
00:34:33,131 --> 00:34:35,901
I'll be on guard duty
in the living room tonight.

547
00:34:36,501 --> 00:34:37,501
Like this.

548
00:34:43,741 --> 00:34:44,741
You scared me.

549
00:34:45,781 --> 00:34:48,211
So, you're sleeping
in this room from now on?

550
00:34:49,611 --> 00:34:52,421
I don't know. Why's Hyun Bin
treating me like this?

551
00:34:53,181 --> 00:34:55,221
Hyun Bin? What about him?

552
00:34:55,551 --> 00:34:57,321
I don't know. Forget it.

553
00:35:13,471 --> 00:35:17,471
Practice speaking up
about what you truly want.

554
00:35:18,611 --> 00:35:21,111
- Honey.
- Yes, I'm right here!

555
00:35:21,651 --> 00:35:22,911
Just tell me whatever you need.

556
00:35:24,181 --> 00:35:25,451
You can take some blankets...

557
00:35:26,021 --> 00:35:27,621
and sleep on the floor.

558
00:35:28,991 --> 00:35:30,021
The floor?

559
00:35:30,651 --> 00:35:33,161
That's what I'd like you to do.

560
00:35:34,961 --> 00:35:36,031
Okay then.

561
00:35:43,001 --> 00:35:44,301
But the floor's so cold...

562
00:35:49,671 --> 00:35:52,641
What is it? What's going on?
What did you want to talk about?

563
00:35:53,111 --> 00:35:55,211
I need your opinion
on something, Mom.

564
00:35:56,611 --> 00:35:57,621
What's this?

565
00:35:57,921 --> 00:36:01,821
It's an offer from Yang Hyun Bin.
To launch my own brand.

566
00:36:02,451 --> 00:36:06,621
- Director Yang did?
- Yes. He guarantees total control,

567
00:36:06,691 --> 00:36:09,391
and he's offering
to fully fund the budget.

568
00:36:09,791 --> 00:36:14,101
- As a personal offer?
- No, it's a company partnership.

569
00:36:15,931 --> 00:36:17,271
And what do you want to do?

570
00:36:19,301 --> 00:36:21,641
Honestly, as a designer,

571
00:36:21,711 --> 00:36:24,341
I'd obviously rather launch my own
brand than work for a company.

572
00:36:24,911 --> 00:36:27,381
Especially with backing this strong.

573
00:36:28,711 --> 00:36:29,881
You know that next week,

574
00:36:30,411 --> 00:36:33,151
your uncle is registering
his marriage, right?

575
00:36:33,581 --> 00:36:36,821
I know. I know we can't be together,
better than anyone.

576
00:36:37,421 --> 00:36:40,121
Besides, Yang Hyun Bin
is so cold and distant.

577
00:36:41,991 --> 00:36:43,431
So you decide for me, Mom.

578
00:36:43,691 --> 00:36:47,101
From now on, I won't act without
your and the family's consent.

579
00:36:51,241 --> 00:36:54,671
Thank you for telling me about this
and not keeping it a secret.

580
00:36:57,941 --> 00:37:00,611
It does seem like
a great opportunity,

581
00:37:01,411 --> 00:37:02,681
but on one condition.

582
00:37:03,151 --> 00:37:06,951
We won't date. Absolutely.
No romantic feelings, just business.

583
00:37:07,051 --> 00:37:09,621
- Okay?
- No, not that.

584
00:37:10,051 --> 00:37:11,421
Then what is it?

585
00:37:14,931 --> 00:37:17,131
What? What sort of partner?

586
00:37:18,061 --> 00:37:19,401
A business partner.

587
00:37:20,131 --> 00:37:22,431
Getting back together
under the guise of business?

588
00:37:23,031 --> 00:37:24,641
You evil.

589
00:37:25,741 --> 00:37:29,471
I have no personal feelings for her.
Not even one percent.

590
00:37:29,811 --> 00:37:30,911
No double in-laws.

591
00:37:31,881 --> 00:37:33,511
Over my dead body.

592
00:37:33,881 --> 00:37:35,451
Of course, Father.

593
00:37:36,781 --> 00:37:38,521
Don't worry. That won't happen.

594
00:37:38,951 --> 00:37:42,621
And I'm not asking for permission.
I'm telling you.

595
00:37:43,621 --> 00:37:45,621
- Oh my.
- You know that...

596
00:37:45,621 --> 00:37:47,191
you're being very rude, right?

597
00:37:47,291 --> 00:37:51,101
Don't you think I have the right?
Think of everything Mother's done.

598
00:37:51,731 --> 00:37:52,901
Gosh, unbelievable...

599
00:37:53,461 --> 00:37:57,171
Listen. If this causes more trouble
with Dr. Gong's family,

600
00:37:57,231 --> 00:37:59,001
I'm not putting up with it anymore.

601
00:38:04,981 --> 00:38:06,541
I got their permission. Happy now?

602
00:38:07,311 --> 00:38:09,211
Let's meet up later
and sign the contract.

603
00:38:10,511 --> 00:38:12,221
- Min Seo.
- Yes?

604
00:38:12,281 --> 00:38:14,181
- Take care. See you again.
- Okay.

605
00:38:14,251 --> 00:38:15,251
Keep in touch, okay?

606
00:38:16,191 --> 00:38:17,491
All right, I'm leaving.

607
00:38:23,061 --> 00:38:24,361
Aunt Dong Suk, hurry up.

608
00:38:26,061 --> 00:38:29,571
Se Ri, you remembered helping me
with my shoot today, didn't you?

609
00:38:29,831 --> 00:38:33,401
What? Right. I'll head over later.

610
00:38:34,441 --> 00:38:35,511
Thanks.

611
00:38:44,551 --> 00:38:45,551
Oh my.

612
00:38:45,921 --> 00:38:48,021
What's all this gimbap for?

613
00:38:48,551 --> 00:38:52,261
Dae Han said he has a shoot today
and Jeong Han's going to the police,

614
00:38:52,361 --> 00:38:53,391
so I thought I'd pack them some.

615
00:38:54,121 --> 00:38:56,191
Has there been any progress
with the investigation?

616
00:38:56,931 --> 00:38:59,431
How would we know?
We just have to wait.

617
00:39:00,301 --> 00:39:02,001
By the way,
what about Director Yang?

618
00:39:02,001 --> 00:39:03,001
I bet they said no, right?

619
00:39:03,331 --> 00:39:05,801
He said he got
his family's permission.

620
00:39:06,271 --> 00:39:08,511
- Really?
- What are you guys talking about?

621
00:39:08,771 --> 00:39:12,741
Apparently, Director Yang and Ju Ah
are going into business together.

622
00:39:13,611 --> 00:39:14,611
What?

623
00:39:15,151 --> 00:39:19,281
Grandma, don't worry about a thing,
so just forget about it, okay?

624
00:39:20,581 --> 00:39:25,191
I wonder if my talk
softened them up. How unexpected.

625
00:39:25,391 --> 00:39:28,291
Don't even wonder about it.
It'll just stress you out again.

626
00:39:32,531 --> 00:39:34,201
This is getting serious.

627
00:39:36,171 --> 00:39:38,001
I think we should let
Dr. Gong's family know.

628
00:39:38,071 --> 00:39:39,071
Right.

629
00:39:39,341 --> 00:39:40,601
(Respect for Human Rights,
Fairness, and Kindness)

630
00:39:40,701 --> 00:39:43,711
It's me again. Hi, everyone.

631
00:39:44,011 --> 00:39:47,341
I brought some gimbap for you all.
Please, have some.

632
00:39:47,411 --> 00:39:49,811
- You've come at the perfect time.
- Pardon?

633
00:39:50,081 --> 00:39:53,351
We checked Jo Mi Hyang's family
and found she has an older brother.

634
00:39:53,481 --> 00:39:57,351
- Jo Mun Sik.
- You mean Jo Mun Sik is real?

635
00:39:58,491 --> 00:40:02,391
Then how could my father
have lived as Jo Mun Sik?

636
00:40:02,831 --> 00:40:07,101
All traces of Jo Mun Sik disappeared
about 30 years ago.

637
00:40:07,631 --> 00:40:10,331
No missing person report,
no death certificate.

638
00:40:11,371 --> 00:40:13,241
What does that...

639
00:40:13,301 --> 00:40:16,741
The team confirmed that 30 years ago
Jo Mun Sik's registered address...

640
00:40:17,041 --> 00:40:18,041
was in Wolseon-dong.

641
00:40:18,611 --> 00:40:21,351
- Wolseon-dong?
- That's right.

642
00:40:21,711 --> 00:40:24,881
You said his last house call was in
Wolseon-dong, didn't you?

643
00:40:25,081 --> 00:40:26,081
Yes.

644
00:40:27,021 --> 00:40:30,191
Then, don't tell me that patient,
the one who fell...

645
00:40:30,891 --> 00:40:32,391
was Jo Mun Sik?

646
00:40:32,721 --> 00:40:36,191
We believe Jo Mi Hyang testified
that the doctor never came.

647
00:40:37,291 --> 00:40:41,031
- Oh my...
- Jo Mun Sik died from that fall,

648
00:40:41,471 --> 00:40:46,401
and that Jo Mi Hyang may have
swapped identities with your father.

649
00:40:46,941 --> 00:40:48,571
That's the theory the detectives
are working with for now.

650
00:40:49,041 --> 00:40:50,571
But how could she...

651
00:40:50,641 --> 00:40:54,411
We're looking into kidnapping,
hiding a death, or body disposal.

652
00:40:54,911 --> 00:40:58,351
A nationwide APB will be issued
for Jo Mi Hyang, a flight risk.

653
00:40:59,481 --> 00:41:03,391
Does that mean
my father could be in danger too?

654
00:41:03,821 --> 00:41:08,331
If she's cornered, she might commit
more crimes to destroy evidence.

655
00:41:10,831 --> 00:41:11,831
Oh no. What am I going to do?

656
00:41:12,501 --> 00:41:15,231
Oh, my. They haven't bloomed yet.

657
00:41:15,931 --> 00:41:18,171
(Kim Man Hee's Beauty Salon)

658
00:41:18,401 --> 00:41:19,571
- Detective Cha.
- Yes.

659
00:41:19,641 --> 00:41:21,071
- Here you go.
- Thanks.

660
00:41:21,941 --> 00:41:22,941
Excuse me, ma'am?

661
00:41:23,611 --> 00:41:26,511
We'd like to ask you some questions.
Do you recognize this woman?

662
00:41:27,341 --> 00:41:31,051
Her name is Jo Mi Hyang.
We heard she had a tailor shop here.

663
00:41:31,351 --> 00:41:32,721
Have you seen her around recently?

664
00:41:33,781 --> 00:41:36,951
- I don't think I've seen her.
- So you don't know her?

665
00:41:45,561 --> 00:41:46,561
Mun Sik.

666
00:41:47,661 --> 00:41:49,731
Mun Sik. Hurry!

667
00:41:58,181 --> 00:42:00,811
What happened? What's wrong?

668
00:42:01,851 --> 00:42:05,321
The police.
They're swarming the place.

669
00:42:06,251 --> 00:42:08,051
Fine, I'll turn myself in.

670
00:42:09,151 --> 00:42:10,151
What?

671
00:42:10,221 --> 00:42:13,521
I'd rather turn myself in
than keep hiding like this.

672
00:42:14,261 --> 00:42:15,261
Then what about me?

673
00:42:15,861 --> 00:42:19,931
If you get arrested, so will I
for harboring a murderer!

674
00:42:20,001 --> 00:42:22,701
I'm the murderer.
I won't mention you.

675
00:42:23,001 --> 00:42:25,371
I'll just say
I did it all on my own.

676
00:42:25,571 --> 00:42:29,471
Don't be ridiculous.
Just hurry up and pack. Hurry.

677
00:42:32,911 --> 00:42:33,941
Hurry up!

678
00:42:34,981 --> 00:42:35,981
Yes, Jeong Han.

679
00:42:38,751 --> 00:42:40,321
Okay, I got it.

680
00:42:40,881 --> 00:42:43,491
Jeong Han,
let's not tell Mom about this.

681
00:42:45,621 --> 00:42:47,561
Yes, okay. Yes.

682
00:42:52,401 --> 00:42:55,071
What is it?
Did you hear anything about Father?

683
00:42:55,431 --> 00:42:56,431
Yes.

684
00:42:57,001 --> 00:43:00,041
But there's nothing we can do,
and it's so frustrating.

685
00:43:00,641 --> 00:43:02,311
Maybe we should have postponed
the photo shoot.

686
00:43:02,771 --> 00:43:06,041
It's okay. When Father gets here,
I want to show him these photos.

687
00:43:07,981 --> 00:43:08,981
Anyway, I just hope...

688
00:43:09,611 --> 00:43:13,721
I don't look too stiff.
Like this, right? Look.

689
00:43:13,851 --> 00:43:14,851
Like this.

690
00:43:16,291 --> 00:43:18,691
- Dong Suk!
- You made it!

691
00:43:18,761 --> 00:43:21,061
Se Ri, thanks so much for coming.

692
00:43:21,121 --> 00:43:24,091
Are you kidding?
I had to see you in your dress.

693
00:43:24,161 --> 00:43:25,301
I'm so excited.

694
00:43:26,861 --> 00:43:31,441
- Let's go get changed too, Ji Hu.
- Okay.

695
00:43:33,071 --> 00:43:34,541
Hey, can you give me a hand?

696
00:43:35,141 --> 00:43:36,311
- Oh my.
- This way, come on.

697
00:43:36,371 --> 00:43:37,371
Wait, wait, what's happening?

698
00:43:40,441 --> 00:43:41,451
Oh my goodness.

699
00:43:42,251 --> 00:43:44,951
Oh my gosh, Dong Suk,
the dress is so beautiful.

700
00:43:45,251 --> 00:43:46,251
It's a little plain,
don't you think?

701
00:43:46,521 --> 00:43:50,791
No way. For someone your age,
anything too poofy would look tacky.

702
00:43:51,491 --> 00:43:56,131
Wow, it's so elegant and beautiful.
You picked the perfect dress.

703
00:43:56,661 --> 00:43:58,061
Why don't you try it on?

704
00:43:58,801 --> 00:44:01,601
Me? Oh, no. Why would I do that?

705
00:44:01,731 --> 00:44:05,941
You've never gotten to wear one.
You just registered your marriage.

706
00:44:06,301 --> 00:44:10,111
Still, how could I wear your dress?
No, it's okay.

707
00:44:11,271 --> 00:44:14,241
Just do it.
It's only the two of us here, right?

708
00:44:14,311 --> 00:44:15,711
- Come on, hurry. Here.
- Gosh...

709
00:44:16,111 --> 00:44:17,111
Come on!

710
00:44:22,751 --> 00:44:25,161
- Goodness.
- Wow, look at you.

711
00:44:25,621 --> 00:44:27,721
You look so elegant and beautiful.

712
00:44:27,961 --> 00:44:32,301
- I feel a little awkward, Dong Suk.
- Awkward?

713
00:44:32,601 --> 00:44:33,731
You look just like a blushing bride.

714
00:44:34,131 --> 00:44:36,171
All right, that's enough.
It's your turn to wear it now.

715
00:44:36,231 --> 00:44:39,501
Hey, wait. Just a minute, hold on.
Come here, just for a second.

716
00:44:59,961 --> 00:45:01,491
- Surprise!
- Surprise!

717
00:45:07,161 --> 00:45:10,231
- Do you, the groom, Yang Dong Ik.
- Take the bride, Cha Se Ri.

718
00:45:10,331 --> 00:45:11,941
- To love and cherish...
- To love and cherish...

719
00:45:11,941 --> 00:45:13,541
- for the rest of your lives?
- for the rest of your lives?

720
00:45:16,241 --> 00:45:17,241
I do.

721
00:45:18,181 --> 00:45:19,181
All this time,

722
00:45:19,541 --> 00:45:20,881
thank you for putting up with
a flawed man like me...

723
00:45:21,611 --> 00:45:23,381
and staying by my side
all this time.

724
00:45:24,251 --> 00:45:27,081
I'll spend my life making sure
you never regret this.

725
00:45:28,151 --> 00:45:29,321
I promise I'll be good to you.

726
00:45:33,591 --> 00:45:34,591
My beloved,

727
00:45:35,091 --> 00:45:36,091
will you accept my love?

728
00:45:42,771 --> 00:45:44,801
What is all this? Seriously.

729
00:45:48,971 --> 00:45:50,011
I love you, Se Ri!

730
00:45:57,851 --> 00:45:58,921
Mom, you look so beautiful!

731
00:46:04,221 --> 00:46:07,291
Okay, could you two
scooch in a little closer?

732
00:46:07,721 --> 00:46:08,731
Okay.

733
00:46:09,761 --> 00:46:10,891
Yes, perfect.

734
00:46:12,131 --> 00:46:14,061
Now, I'd like you
to look at each other.

735
00:46:14,231 --> 00:46:16,031
- Look at her?
- Yes, that's right.

736
00:46:19,301 --> 00:46:20,541
- Look at him.
- Dad.

737
00:46:20,841 --> 00:46:24,111
- Dad, why are you so nervous?
- It's thanks to the girls that...

738
00:46:25,141 --> 00:46:27,011
we're finally having
a wedding photoshoot.

739
00:46:27,881 --> 00:46:28,881
That we are.

740
00:46:29,711 --> 00:46:33,281
Wow.
Honey, you look so beautiful today.

741
00:46:34,221 --> 00:46:35,291
Surprise.

742
00:46:37,951 --> 00:46:39,991
Hey, Eun Bin. Min Seo.

743
00:46:40,521 --> 00:46:42,591
- Let's get a picture together.
- What?

744
00:46:42,661 --> 00:46:45,161
Of course we need a picture
with our girls. Come on in.

745
00:46:45,231 --> 00:46:48,031
- Really?
- Sounds good!

746
00:46:51,201 --> 00:46:52,501
Should we look over there? Okay.

747
00:46:56,471 --> 00:46:57,471
Gosh, Dad.

748
00:46:57,971 --> 00:47:00,241
With us? This is for you and Mom.

749
00:47:08,291 --> 00:47:09,891
- Say cheese!
- Okay.

750
00:47:10,651 --> 00:47:11,661
That's lovely.

751
00:47:17,631 --> 00:47:18,631
Perfect.

752
00:47:19,601 --> 00:47:20,601
Switch it up, switch it up!

753
00:47:30,211 --> 00:47:33,781
I've grown so fond of you, Min Seo.
I'm sad to see you go.

754
00:47:34,141 --> 00:47:35,151
Me too.

755
00:47:35,811 --> 00:47:38,721
I'm going to miss you all so much.

756
00:47:40,081 --> 00:47:43,451
Make sure you keep in touch with Mom
once you're there.

757
00:47:43,621 --> 00:47:45,861
Study hard
and become a doctor, okay?

758
00:47:46,491 --> 00:47:47,491
I will, Grandfather.

759
00:47:48,391 --> 00:47:52,761
For welcoming me into your family,
thank you so much.

760
00:47:53,161 --> 00:47:55,901
I should be thanking you
for coming into Se Ri's life.

761
00:47:57,931 --> 00:48:00,371
And if you ever want
to come see your mom,

762
00:48:00,941 --> 00:48:02,771
I'll get you a plane ticket
in a heartbeat.

763
00:48:02,941 --> 00:48:06,211
Just let me, your stepdad,
know, anytime.

764
00:48:08,711 --> 00:48:10,811
Okay. Thank you, Stepdad.

765
00:48:18,491 --> 00:48:21,831
I thought you'd be a complete mess,
but you're surprisingly calm.

766
00:48:22,161 --> 00:48:23,161
Come on.

767
00:48:23,891 --> 00:48:25,561
We'll see her again.

768
00:48:27,061 --> 00:48:28,571
I'm trying not to think
of it as a real goodbye.

769
00:48:30,131 --> 00:48:32,701
That's right.
We're going to see her again,

770
00:48:32,941 --> 00:48:35,541
so why is everyone acting
like this is the final goodbye?

771
00:48:36,641 --> 00:48:38,681
- Are you crying?
- No, I'm not!

772
00:48:41,381 --> 00:48:44,481
You know
I'm most grateful to you, right?

773
00:48:45,281 --> 00:48:50,221
If it weren't for you,
I never would've met my mom,

774
00:48:51,051 --> 00:48:53,591
or this wonderful family.

775
00:48:55,161 --> 00:48:56,761
I'm so grateful...

776
00:48:57,291 --> 00:48:59,161
and so happy that you're my sister.

777
00:49:02,171 --> 00:49:04,601
Min Seo, don't go.

778
00:49:06,871 --> 00:49:09,641
- Don't cry.
- I'll miss you.

779
00:49:09,971 --> 00:49:11,711
We'll just see each other again.

780
00:49:12,141 --> 00:49:14,711
How long's the flight? I'm coming.

781
00:49:14,711 --> 00:49:16,311
- Want to come with me?
- Yes!

782
00:49:16,811 --> 00:49:19,151
- Dad, I want to go too!
- Sure, go ahead.

783
00:49:20,421 --> 00:49:21,421
(Business Cooperation
and Brand Operation Agreement)

784
00:49:21,421 --> 00:49:24,021
I'll accept your business
partnership proposal.

785
00:49:25,321 --> 00:49:27,421
- Should we make it official?
- Not yet.

786
00:49:28,361 --> 00:49:31,591
I've added clauses to the contract,
including one about a workspace.

787
00:49:32,801 --> 00:49:36,031
A workspace is a given, of course.
Tell me what you're looking for,

788
00:49:36,171 --> 00:49:37,571
and I'll find something
for you ASAP.

789
00:49:38,031 --> 00:49:41,271
No, there are a few vacant spaces
near my place,

790
00:49:41,341 --> 00:49:42,571
so I'll check them out
and set it up myself.

791
00:49:43,011 --> 00:49:44,011
Okay.

792
00:49:44,971 --> 00:49:48,811
We must start on samples right away.
What's the staffing plan?

793
00:49:49,151 --> 00:49:50,151
Am I supposed to hire them myself?

794
00:49:50,351 --> 00:49:53,621
No, that will be handled this week.
Is this all?

795
00:49:54,651 --> 00:49:56,121
Read the last clause.

796
00:49:59,291 --> 00:50:01,291
("Personal relations outside of work
must not interfere with business.")

797
00:50:01,361 --> 00:50:03,591
"Personal relationships
outside of work..."

798
00:50:03,891 --> 00:50:06,831
"must not interfere with business."

799
00:50:07,901 --> 00:50:08,901
Okay?

800
00:50:09,471 --> 00:50:11,671
- Do we have to?
- What?

801
00:50:11,771 --> 00:50:13,841
We're already over.
What more are you expecting?

802
00:50:17,841 --> 00:50:18,881
Fine, whatever. Okay.

803
00:50:19,381 --> 00:50:21,981
All right then.
Do we have a deal, CEO Gong?

804
00:50:22,411 --> 00:50:25,751
Since this is purely professional,
let's keep it formal.

805
00:50:26,721 --> 00:50:28,851
Yes, of course.

806
00:50:30,391 --> 00:50:31,391
Right.

807
00:50:32,661 --> 00:50:33,661
Right.

808
00:50:47,671 --> 00:50:48,671
What's important...

809
00:50:49,041 --> 00:50:52,581
is that you recognize and respond
to your wife's emotions.

810
00:50:53,441 --> 00:50:54,441
Honey.

811
00:50:55,651 --> 00:50:56,651
Yes?

812
00:50:57,481 --> 00:50:59,281
Should we sleep
in separate rooms tonight?

813
00:51:00,521 --> 00:51:03,651
Why? Do you want the bed tonight?

814
00:51:04,291 --> 00:51:05,291
No.

815
00:51:06,161 --> 00:51:08,061
You sleep with Min Seo.

816
00:51:09,161 --> 00:51:10,991
It's your last night with Min Seo.

817
00:51:22,471 --> 00:51:25,011
All this time, I've been saying
how much I love you,

818
00:51:25,941 --> 00:51:27,941
but I was so oblivious
to how you were feeling.

819
00:51:29,251 --> 00:51:32,081
To send away the child you carried
and gave birth to,

820
00:51:32,951 --> 00:51:35,621
I can't imagine how much
you must have ached to see her.

821
00:51:36,721 --> 00:51:38,861
If only you had opened up
to me sooner,

822
00:51:39,961 --> 00:51:43,291
we could've called her more often
and even visited.

823
00:51:44,461 --> 00:51:45,461
I'm sorry.

824
00:51:46,531 --> 00:51:47,531
I was not someone...

825
00:51:48,131 --> 00:51:50,031
you could lean on.

826
00:51:51,001 --> 00:51:52,101
For all those years,

827
00:51:53,041 --> 00:51:55,041
I made you endure it all alone.

828
00:51:56,571 --> 00:51:57,571
I'm truly sorry.

829
00:52:00,611 --> 00:52:02,051
Before Min Seo falls asleep,

830
00:52:03,051 --> 00:52:04,051
you should go to her.

831
00:52:23,171 --> 00:52:24,331
Thank you, honey.

832
00:52:32,641 --> 00:52:33,741
No, thank you.

833
00:52:40,081 --> 00:52:42,891
Mom, you two didn't fight again,
did you?

834
00:52:43,151 --> 00:52:44,221
No, of course not.

835
00:52:44,491 --> 00:52:46,861
Your stepdad sent me in here
to sleep with you.

836
00:52:47,161 --> 00:52:48,161
Good.

837
00:52:49,091 --> 00:52:52,001
Mom, there's something
I wanted to tell you.

838
00:52:53,731 --> 00:52:54,731
What is it?

839
00:52:55,031 --> 00:52:59,571
After I leave tomorrow,
I don't want you to be too sad.

840
00:53:00,241 --> 00:53:03,111
I'm going to be strong
and do great over there,

841
00:53:03,371 --> 00:53:06,911
so you shouldn't worry about me.
I just want you to be happy.

842
00:53:08,581 --> 00:53:09,751
My sweet girl.

843
00:53:10,611 --> 00:53:13,021
Worrying about your mom
right up until you leave?

844
00:53:14,081 --> 00:53:16,521
How can you not resent me,
not even once?

845
00:53:16,791 --> 00:53:19,791
Why would I resent you, Mom?

846
00:53:20,491 --> 00:53:24,661
The only reason I'm here is because
you didn't give up on me and had me.

847
00:53:28,061 --> 00:53:29,071
If I had been...

848
00:53:32,671 --> 00:53:34,641
better off,

849
00:53:35,711 --> 00:53:38,011
I never would have sent you away.

850
00:53:39,411 --> 00:53:41,381
And you wouldn't have
had to grow up...

851
00:53:42,581 --> 00:53:44,481
trying to be so tough.

852
00:53:44,851 --> 00:53:46,921
Come on, Mom.

853
00:53:48,281 --> 00:53:49,291
I just keep...

854
00:53:52,161 --> 00:53:54,261
thinking about the day
I had to give you up.

855
00:53:56,061 --> 00:53:57,261
The thought that I might
never see you...

856
00:53:58,801 --> 00:54:00,461
or hold you again...

857
00:54:02,331 --> 00:54:03,471
The pain was so real,

858
00:54:04,231 --> 00:54:07,571
agonizing, like a part of me
was being torn away.

859
00:54:09,941 --> 00:54:10,941
And now I have to...

860
00:54:12,941 --> 00:54:14,941
have to send you away
all over again.

861
00:54:17,351 --> 00:54:18,351
Mom.

862
00:54:19,221 --> 00:54:20,651
It's different this time.

863
00:54:21,881 --> 00:54:26,391
We know where each other are now,
and we can see each other again.

864
00:54:28,761 --> 00:54:29,761
You're right.

865
00:54:31,561 --> 00:54:32,601
Next time...

866
00:54:33,961 --> 00:54:35,931
I promise I'll come see you,
Min Seo.

867
00:54:36,571 --> 00:54:38,871
Okay. I'll be waiting.

868
00:54:41,101 --> 00:54:42,341
My sweet girl.

869
00:54:50,081 --> 00:54:51,081
Until...

870
00:54:51,851 --> 00:54:54,021
we meet again,

871
00:54:54,381 --> 00:54:56,751
let's promise to be healthy
and happy.

872
00:54:57,251 --> 00:54:58,451
Okay, Mom?

873
00:55:23,881 --> 00:55:26,351
Why?
Is the investigation not going well?

874
00:55:28,151 --> 00:55:32,991
- Go on, it's fine.
- It's just...

875
00:55:33,691 --> 00:55:34,691
What?

876
00:55:36,161 --> 00:55:37,161
Yes, Officer Jeong.

877
00:55:38,491 --> 00:55:40,731
Yes, yes. Really?

878
00:55:41,231 --> 00:55:43,901
Yes, I understand. Okay.

879
00:55:45,541 --> 00:55:47,371
There was a tip
on Jo Mi Hyang's whereabouts...

880
00:55:47,371 --> 00:55:48,471
so the police are checking it out.

881
00:55:49,311 --> 00:55:50,971
- Really?
- Yes.

882
00:55:52,881 --> 00:55:53,881
Honey.

883
00:56:03,291 --> 00:56:04,721
Yes, for two people.

884
00:56:05,691 --> 00:56:07,021
You think I have papers?

885
00:56:07,661 --> 00:56:09,431
If I had papers,
why would I need a broker?

886
00:56:11,061 --> 00:56:12,061
Darn it.

887
00:56:14,761 --> 00:56:15,771
I know it's risky.

888
00:56:16,701 --> 00:56:18,871
We have to get out of the country
as fast as possible.

889
00:56:19,501 --> 00:56:21,741
I'll pay whatever it takes.

890
00:56:22,511 --> 00:56:23,841
Whether it's Mokpo or Incheon,

891
00:56:24,211 --> 00:56:26,241
as long as there's a boat,
anywhere is fine.

892
00:56:26,711 --> 00:56:27,881
Hurry. Just hurry.

893
00:56:30,381 --> 00:56:32,721
(Detective)

894
00:56:49,231 --> 00:56:50,231
Darn it.

895
00:56:52,101 --> 00:56:53,101
Looks like they got away.

896
00:57:06,721 --> 00:57:09,691
Why'd you come into work?
The funeral was just yesterday.

897
00:57:10,051 --> 00:57:11,151
You should be home resting.

898
00:57:13,661 --> 00:57:16,231
If I'm alone, I'll just think
about my father more.

899
00:57:18,361 --> 00:57:20,261
How did it go with Lawyer Choi
yesterday?

900
00:57:20,701 --> 00:57:22,001
Oh, that...

901
00:57:23,901 --> 00:57:27,201
My father changed his entire will
right before he passed away,

902
00:57:27,741 --> 00:57:30,941
and since it's all been notarized,
Jun Hyeok's inheritance...

903
00:57:31,011 --> 00:57:32,641
should be transferred
without any issues.

904
00:57:33,981 --> 00:57:36,811
Wow, he really hit the jackpot,
didn't he?

905
00:57:41,281 --> 00:57:43,021
Yes, Manager Kim.

906
00:57:44,221 --> 00:57:45,221
What was that?

907
00:57:47,621 --> 00:57:48,621
Got it.

908
00:57:52,461 --> 00:57:53,461
What is it?

909
00:57:53,931 --> 00:57:56,101
Director Baek has called
an emergency board meeting.

910
00:57:58,231 --> 00:58:00,801
The funeral was just yesterday.
How could he?

911
00:58:01,101 --> 00:58:02,441
We saw this coming.

912
00:58:02,841 --> 00:58:04,811
You're prepared, right?

913
00:58:05,681 --> 00:58:06,681
Yes.

914
00:58:08,781 --> 00:58:10,551
But where on earth is Jun Hyeok?

915
00:58:11,481 --> 00:58:13,481
(Taehan Group)

916
00:58:13,551 --> 00:58:14,621
Well then.

917
00:58:15,621 --> 00:58:17,721
Shall we go shut down
the Fashion Division?

918
00:58:17,791 --> 00:58:19,661
(Director Baek Won Gyu)

919
00:58:29,131 --> 00:58:30,201
Why is he over there?

920
00:58:30,931 --> 00:58:32,001
Hwangbo Jun Hyeok.

921
00:58:35,841 --> 00:58:36,971
What are you doing over there?

922
00:58:37,811 --> 00:58:38,811
Get over here.

923
00:58:57,861 --> 00:59:02,001
I see you so little,
I'm starting to forget your face.

924
00:59:02,731 --> 00:59:05,801
I'm going to be swamped
until we find Dr. Gong.

925
00:59:07,271 --> 00:59:09,671
I mean... Sorry.

926
00:59:10,641 --> 00:59:13,541
What can you do?
By the time the police got there,

927
00:59:13,611 --> 00:59:14,981
I heard she'd already bolted.

928
00:59:15,611 --> 00:59:16,611
Yes.

929
00:59:17,151 --> 00:59:20,651
Dr. Gong and Ms. Na
are beyond disappointed.

930
00:59:21,451 --> 00:59:24,721
It's too soon to be disappointed.
We're doing everything we can.

931
00:59:27,661 --> 00:59:28,691
What?

932
00:59:29,231 --> 00:59:30,391
Just getting a good look
while I can.

933
00:59:30,761 --> 00:59:33,331
- Hold still for a second.
- Hang on.

934
00:59:35,831 --> 00:59:36,871
Yes?

935
00:59:37,371 --> 00:59:38,371
What?

936
00:59:39,901 --> 00:59:40,901
What is it?

937
00:59:44,141 --> 00:59:45,941
She's trying to stow away?

938
00:59:46,511 --> 00:59:51,111
Yes, we confirmed she contacted
a broker in China this morning.

939
00:59:51,251 --> 00:59:53,021
What do you mean, stowing away?

940
00:59:53,421 --> 00:59:54,781
- Mom!
- Mom!

941
00:59:54,981 --> 00:59:57,051
She can't exactly leave
the country legally.

942
00:59:57,691 --> 01:00:02,091
Also, we tracked her car heading
in the direction of Incheon Port,

943
01:00:02,261 --> 01:00:05,531
so our detective team is on standby
at the port entrance.

944
01:00:07,061 --> 01:00:10,631
So please, try not to worry.
I'll call you as soon as I get news.

945
01:00:11,501 --> 01:00:13,971
- We're counting on you.
- Of course.

946
01:00:16,771 --> 01:00:17,771
Mom.

947
01:00:22,651 --> 01:00:24,151
Where are we going?

948
01:00:24,451 --> 01:00:26,451
Just be quiet.
You're stressing me out.

949
01:00:32,421 --> 01:00:34,691
And what have you been clutching
this whole time?

950
01:00:54,441 --> 01:00:57,751
Come on, why aren't they calling?
Where do I go at Incheon Port?

951
01:00:58,051 --> 01:00:59,281
Did they just take my money
and ditch me?

952
01:01:04,551 --> 01:01:08,621
Oh my goodness.
Mun Sik! Oh my goodness!

953
01:01:08,761 --> 01:01:10,391
Is he crazy? What am I going to do?

954
01:01:13,761 --> 01:01:14,761
Mun Sik!

955
01:01:15,771 --> 01:01:16,871
Mun Sik!

956
01:01:19,401 --> 01:01:21,871
Mun Sik!

957
01:01:22,201 --> 01:01:23,741
Somebody stop him! He's a patient!

958
01:01:24,971 --> 01:01:25,981
Mun Sik!

959
01:01:27,411 --> 01:01:28,441
Why is he so fast?

960
01:01:30,351 --> 01:01:31,351
Mun Sik!

961
01:01:33,681 --> 01:01:36,091
How can he run so fast? Seriously?

962
01:01:50,771 --> 01:01:51,971
Mun Sik!

963
01:02:10,821 --> 01:02:11,821
Yes?

964
01:02:11,891 --> 01:02:14,121
(Warm and Reliable Police)

965
01:02:14,161 --> 01:02:15,161
What?

966
01:02:16,491 --> 01:02:20,231
Really? Okay, got it.

967
01:02:22,161 --> 01:02:25,101
- Did they lose her?
- It's worse than that.

968
01:02:25,401 --> 01:02:27,001
They checked the CCTV footage.

969
01:02:27,371 --> 01:02:31,641
- Dr. Gong jumped from her car.
- What?

970
01:02:32,481 --> 01:02:33,911
So what happened to him after that?

971
01:02:34,141 --> 01:02:37,751
We do not know. They lost her,
and Dr. Gong vanished.

972
01:02:38,011 --> 01:02:39,051
Gosh.

973
01:02:39,851 --> 01:02:42,151
Excuse me, officers.
I've got someone here.

974
01:02:42,621 --> 01:02:44,421
Come on, hurry up, will you?

975
01:02:44,491 --> 01:02:45,551
(Onjeong Police Substation)

976
01:02:45,621 --> 01:02:46,991
This is driving me nuts.

977
01:02:52,261 --> 01:02:53,661
- Mom.
- Oh, dear.

978
01:02:56,631 --> 01:02:57,631
My gosh.

979
01:03:01,371 --> 01:03:03,311
- It's Officer Jeong.
- It is?

980
01:03:04,671 --> 01:03:05,771
Yes, Officer Jeong.

981
01:03:09,141 --> 01:03:10,211
Right now?

982
01:03:11,151 --> 01:03:14,121
Okay. Yes, we understand.

983
01:03:15,381 --> 01:03:18,751
- What is it?
- What did he say?

984
01:03:19,591 --> 01:03:22,161
- He wants us at the station.
- What?

985
01:03:27,361 --> 01:03:29,301
- Chief!
- Yes, hurry. Come on in.

986
01:03:29,371 --> 01:03:31,031
- Okay.
- Hurry.

987
01:03:31,601 --> 01:03:34,641
What is it?
Have you found our father?

988
01:03:34,971 --> 01:03:37,771
Why don't you go inside
and see for yourself first?

989
01:03:39,041 --> 01:03:40,041
Let's go.

990
01:03:41,781 --> 01:03:43,781
(Onjeong Police Substation)

991
01:03:50,621 --> 01:03:52,621
(Onjeong Police Substation)

992
01:04:01,261 --> 01:04:02,301
Jeong Han, can you hear that?

993
01:04:02,931 --> 01:04:04,001
Yes.

994
01:04:04,871 --> 01:04:05,871
Well?

995
01:04:07,341 --> 01:04:08,341
It's him.

996
01:04:09,711 --> 01:04:11,911
- That's our father.
- He is?

997
01:04:11,971 --> 01:04:16,381
(Onjeong Police Substation)

998
01:04:18,511 --> 01:04:20,081
Yes, that's our father!

999
01:04:26,961 --> 01:04:28,161
Father...

1000
01:04:31,131 --> 01:04:32,631
Father!

1001
01:04:33,101 --> 01:04:34,161
Father.

1002
01:05:12,001 --> 01:05:14,771
(Recipe For Love)

1003
01:05:14,841 --> 01:05:19,011
Betraying me after Father died?
You, of all people!

1004
01:05:19,071 --> 01:05:21,141
It was a decision
for the Group's survival.

1005
01:05:22,141 --> 01:05:25,011
- We need to clean house.
- Starting with Director Yang?

1006
01:05:25,081 --> 01:05:27,021
I was blindsided too.
I'm still reeling.

1007
01:05:27,581 --> 01:05:29,321
You're lower than dirt!

1008
01:05:29,891 --> 01:05:32,761
Do you think Jo Mi Hyang
will show up in Onjeong again?

1009
01:05:32,921 --> 01:05:33,921
Probably.

1010
01:05:34,161 --> 01:05:38,061
- We can catch her, right?
- We have to. No matter what.

1011
01:05:38,131 --> 01:05:41,031
With the blessings of our
guests here today,

1012
01:05:41,131 --> 01:05:44,631
we declare that we are
now husband and wife.

1013
01:05:45,571 --> 01:05:47,901
Live long enough,
and we do meet again.

1014
01:05:49,339 --> 01:05:51,339
Dramaday.me
